132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1104
H.P. 723 House of Representatives, March 18, 2025
An Act to Limit the Liability of Persons Who Provide Firearm Hold
Agreements
Reference to the Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative DOUDERA of Camden.
Cosponsored by Senator TALBOT ROSS of Cumberland and
Representatives: ARATA of New Gloucester, HASENFUS of Readfield, WHITE of Guilford,
Senator: MARTIN of Oxford.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §2017 is enacted to read:
3 §2017. Limitation of liability of holder of firearm under firearm hold agreement
4 A cause of action may not be taken against a person who agreed to hold a firearm under
5 a firearm hold agreement for returning the firearm to the firearm owner at the termination
6 of the agreement. The immunity provided in this section does not apply to otherwise
7 unlawful conduct of the person returning the firearm to the firearm owner under this
8 section. For purposes of this section, "firearm hold agreement" means a written or oral
9 agreement between a firearm owner and another person in which the person at the owner's
10 request takes physical possession of a firearm lawfully possessed by the owner and holds
11 the firearm for an agreed-upon period of time.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill provides immunity to the holder of a firearm pursuant to a firearm hold
1144 agreement who returns the firearm to the firearm owner at the termination of the agreement
1155 unless the conduct of the holder is otherwise unlawful.
